Author: Embleema
Title: [ANN] Embleema, the patient blockchain | Product readyâœ…/Big Pharma Partnershipsâœ…
Body: Not all patients want the responsibility of their health data. But we focus on patients with rare diseases and unmet medical needs. Working with advocacy groups such as cysticfibrosis.com, we surveyed their users. 98% want to own their data and share it along their own terms. More than half are interested in receiving compensation. The PatientTruth app is also accesible to caregivers (e.g., parents) and anyone who the patient chooses to share his data with (e.g., doctor) with consent built-in the blockchain

Author: jamesndungu1
Title: [ANN] Embleema, the patient blockchain | Product readyâœ…/Big Pharma Partnershipsâœ…
Body: I've been researching more about Embleema Project, Its products and the Target market, As a person who is interested in Blockchain and Understands the Important of Big Data, I like what Embleema is doing. In the current modern world, the health industry has produced more data that can only be possible to be tapped in a decentralized environment, ethically. Currently, this market has been commercialized and the users exploited with their data being used without their consent, I believe with the use of blockchain technology - Embleema will change the game.  Opportunities of Big Data in the Pharmeceutical Industry will be a factor in the implementation of Embleema project, With this data being in demand by drugs manufucturers due to the personalization aspects of drugs manufucturing and improvments based on geneitc make-ups, environemtns and patients lifestsyles. If you read about the future of precision medicine ->[Why the Future of Precision Medicine Needs Your Help](http://www.futureofpersonalhealth.com/advocacy/why-the-future-of-precision-medicine-needs-your-help) you will understand why i believe why Embleema is a noble project that will improve the future of drugs manufacturing by eliminating generic one-drug-fits-all.  Good luck to the team and will be following this project closely.
